Definition.WordDefinition: Unclog \Un*clog"\, v. t. [1st pref. un- + clog.] To disencumber of a clog, or of difficulties and obstructions; to free from encumbrances; to set at liberty. --Shak. [1913 Webster]
unclog v : become or cause to become unobstructed; "The chemical that we poured down the drain unclogged it" [ant: {clog}] [also: {unclogging}, {unclogged}]
